==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expostulation
<hw>Ex*pos`tu*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>expostulatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of expostulating or
reasoning with a person in opposition to some impropriety of conduct;
remonstrance; earnest and kindly protest; dissuasion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We must use <qex>expostulation</qex> kindly.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expostulator</ent>⟦br⟧
